## 1. Selenium Java Setup & Basic Test

### A. Install Prerequisites
1. **Java JDK 1.8+**  
   - Download & install from [Adoptium](https://adoptium.net/) or Oracle.  
   - Verify in terminal/cmd:
     ```bash
     java -version
     ```
2. **Eclipse IDE**  
   - Download & install from [eclipse.org](https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/).
3. **Chrome Browser**  
   - Install the latest version if not already present.

### B. Download Selenium & ChromeDriver
1. **Selenium Java**  
   - Download the “Selenium Client & WebDriver Language Bindings (Java)” ZIP from  
     http://www.seleniumhq.org/download  
   - Unzip and place all `.jar` files into your Eclipse project’s `jars/` folder.
2. **ChromeDriver**  
   - Download the matching version from https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads  
   - Unzip `chromedriver.exe` into your project’s `drivers/` folder.

### C. Create Eclipse Project
1. **File → New → Java Project** → **Project name:** `Automation`.
2. **Right-click** on `Automation` → **New → Folder** → name it `jars`; repeat for `drivers`.
3. Copy **all Selenium `.jar` files** into `jars/`, and **chromedriver.exe** into `drivers/`.
4. **Right-click** project → **Build Path → Configure Build Path → Libraries → Add JARs…** → select everything under `jars/`.

### D. Write & Run the “Hello Gmail” Test
1. **Right-click** `src` → **New → Package** → `tests`.
2. **Right-click** `tests` → **New → Class** → `GmailTest`.
3. Paste:
   ```java
   package tests;

   import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
   import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

   public class GmailTest {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           // 1. Point to your driver executable
           System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver",
               "drivers/chromedriver.exe");
           // 2. Launch Chrome
           WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
           // 3. Navigate to Gmail
           driver.get("https://www.gmail.com/");
           // 4. Print page title
           System.out.println("Title is: " + driver.getTitle());
           // 5. Close browser
           driver.quit();
       }
   }
